00:19:34.240 --> 00:19:40.720
times already. They even called the police.&nbsp;
Everyone was looking for me. They arrived to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:19:40.720 --> 00:19:46.800
pick me up at 11:00 in the morning. My assistant&nbsp;
had the keys. He opened the door. They went in,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:19:46.800 --> 00:19:52.400
went to the kitchen to put the kettle on. Then&nbsp;
my friend says, "We need to wake Kirsten up. We&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:19:52.400 --> 00:20:00.080
have to go to the airport." The bedroom door was&nbsp;
open. They go in and I'm not there. Slippers are&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:20:00.080 --> 00:20:06.000
in place. Phones are in place. They check the&nbsp;
bathroom and every other room in the apartment,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:20:06.000 --> 00:20:13.360
but well, I wasn't there. The balcony door was&nbsp;
open and that's it. They went downstairs, asked&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:20:13.360 --> 00:20:19.760
the security, and he said, "Well, I didn't see him&nbsp;
leave anywhere. The building isn't very big." They&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:20:19.760 --> 00:20:25.680
checked the video cameras. No one arrived or&nbsp;
left. No one flew out, but the camera wasn't&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:20:25.680 --> 00:20:32.640
looking at the sky. Mostly at the entrance and&nbsp;
exit, and for a whole hour, they were searching,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:20:32.640 --> 00:20:43.280
wondering where I was. Vasili, how long have you&nbsp;
worked with uh Kanan Yumab? about uh 40 years.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:20:43.280 --> 00:20:50.000
Wow. 40 years. Amazing. So very long history.&nbsp;
You guys are very close. Yes. What happened&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:20:50.000 --> 00:20:59.360
on the night of September 17th, 1997? Well, that&nbsp;
was a long time ago. The driver, a mutual friend,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:20:59.360 --> 00:21:04.960
and I went to his apartment. We were supposed to&nbsp;
take him to the airport. He was flying out at 1:00&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:21:04.960 --> 00:21:12.400
in the afternoon that day to Alista, which is the&nbsp;
capital of Kalikia. When we arrived at the house,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:21:12.400 --> 00:21:18.960
I called him on the phone, but he didn't answer.&nbsp;
So, I decided to go up to the apartment. I had my&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:21:18.960 --> 00:21:26.320
own keys. I rang the bell first. He didn't open. I&nbsp;
unlocked the apartment with my key, went into one&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:21:26.320 --> 00:21:33.280
room, then another. He wasn't there. Not in the&nbsp;
kitchen either. Then I saw his clothes hanging.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:21:33.280 --> 00:21:40.960
Two mobile phones were lying on the nightstand.&nbsp;
I was surprised. Where did he go? So I called my&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:21:40.960 --> 00:21:48.080
friend up. I said, "Something weird is going on.&nbsp;
We have a situation. His things are here, but he's&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:21:48.080 --> 00:21:55.520
nowhere to be found." Then some time passed, maybe&nbsp;
an hour, and suddenly he appears from the bedroom,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:21:55.520 --> 00:22:01.520
even though he wasn't there before. I was&nbsp;
so surprised. Where did you come from,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:22:01.520 --> 00:22:10.240
Kersonen? You weren't here. He laughed and said,&nbsp;
"Well, aliens took me." And after a certain time,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:22:10.240 --> 00:22:16.240
I just came out of the bedroom and went to the&nbsp;
bathroom. They followed me into the bathroom and&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:22:16.240 --> 00:22:25.600
started touching me like, "Are you alive or not?"&nbsp;
I said, "Alive?" "Well, where were you?" I said,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:22:25.600 --> 00:22:31.520
"I was flying with friends. They were showing&nbsp;
me their ship or something like that. Yes,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:22:31.520 --> 00:22:38.080
I was in space. Well, that's interesting. They&nbsp;
say, "No, you're probably joking." I say, "No,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:22:38.080 --> 00:22:47.200
it's true." When Keran came back down on the ship,&nbsp;
um, or however he got back into that room and you&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:22:47.200 --> 00:22:53.440
asked him what had happened, he said to you,&nbsp;
"I was taken by extraterrestrials." And then&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:22:53.440 --> 00:22:58.560
at that point, did you ask a lot of follow-up&nbsp;
